Sentencas: Pure YSZ (8 mol% yttria stabilized zirconia) and Fe-doped (2 mol% and 4 mol%) YSZ electrolytes were prepared and sintered at 1200 degrees C and 1400 degrees C, respectively by solid state method.
Titulo: The effect of Fe doping on the properties of SOFC electrolyte YSZ

Sentencas: Their crystal structure, microstructure, sintering behavior, electrical conductivity, and performance as SOFC electrolyte were investigated.
Titulo: The effect of Fe doping on the properties of SOFC electrolyte YSZ

Sentencas: Fe can be dissolved into YSZ lattice and decrease the lattice parameter.
Titulo: The effect of Fe doping on the properties of SOFC electrolyte YSZ

Sentencas: When sintered at 1200 degrees C, Fe dopant can make the YSZ electrolyte denser and increase its total conductivity.
Titulo: The effect of Fe doping on the properties of SOFC electrolyte YSZ

Sentencas: When sintered at 1400 degrees C, the total conductivities of samples decrease for higher Fe dopant concentrations though the densities of samples increase.
Titulo: The effect of Fe doping on the properties of SOFC electrolyte YSZ

Sentencas: All the SOFCs with Fe-doped YSZ electrolytes show better performance than those with Fe-free electrolytes.
Titulo: The effect of Fe doping on the properties of SOFC electrolyte YSZ

Sentencas: The mechanisms of the effect of Fe doping on the properties of YSZ were analyzed.
Titulo: The effect of Fe doping on the properties of SOFC electrolyte YSZ
